      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Star Kiwi MARKETPLACE NZ (11) cops the outside barrier for his Australian debut but he is a multiple Group 1 winner in his homeland and is targeting some big races over the winter. Got a taste of this circuit when he won a trial here last week and has the class to overcome the draw. HI MANAMEISJEFF NZ (10) has been runner-up to star stablemate Captains Mistress in his two runs since a Listed win here, getting within 1.4m of her last week. Better known as a miler but it is important to note he has won all four attempts over this longer distance. DOUBLE LOU (7) has had 10 weeks off since his Riverina Championships placing, ending a campaign that saw him win four races here including the Hondo Grattan. Flies fresh, winning all three attempts and should be ready to go again off two trials. Renshaw Cup winner UBETCHA TIGERPIE (9) returns off a WA raid that saw him finish fourth in both the Nullabor and Fremantle Cup. Draws wide but was runner-up to Marketplace at the trials.",
